item.title: CVE-2022-4443|2024-08-03T01:41:44.426Z -- unknown -- brutebank
item.description: The BruteBank WordPress plugin before 1.9 does not have CSRF check in place when updating its settings, which could allow attackers to make a logged-in admin change them via a CSRF attack.
